<div class="g4">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><img src="/media/13049265/grostl.png" alt="Grostl" width="490" height="280" rel="490,280" /><br /><span style="color: #023761; font-weight: bold;"><a data-udi="umb://document/20b0f077e9d041dcaa08395532079aca" href="/{localLink:umb://document/20b0f077e9d041dcaa08395532079aca}" title="Insider's Guide: Top 5 Mountain Dishes">Quick guide: Top 5 Mountain Dishes</a></span><br />Let’s face it: everyone loves food and the great thing about a ski holiday is that you need to eat MORE than usual to keep your energy levels up to prepare you for a full day of cruising down the slopes. So if that means eating the odd tartiflette, raclette or tiroler grostl here and there, then so be it.</p>
